  <span id="freeText13483297832361066679" style="display:none">Heinlein is one author that seems to read better within his own time than more contemporary ones. When I was in high school in the late 60s / early 70s, *everyone* (except the jocks / cheerleaders) carried/was reading (and grokking) Stranger in a Strange Land. I do still like his works but agree that Moon may actually stand as the better work.</span>
